The paper proposes a deep neural architecture for predicting future Opioid incidences, which involves learning spatio-temporal variations in the data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with data related to public health, which could fall under the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. The use of predictive analytics for decision making also suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also deals with drug-related deaths, which could fall under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with time-series data, which could fall under the Scientific Computing (cs.SD) sub-category.
